<li>Second semester sophomore class standing and completion of most General Education or Foundation classes.</li>
<li>Soc 111- Introduction to Sociology or Soc 112-Social Problems with a B- grade or better.</li>
<li>SW 260-Introduction to Social Work with a B- grade or better.</li>
<li>FDMath223 or Math 221C Statistics with a C- grade or better.</li>
<li>Bio 264- Anatomy and Physiology or Bio 230-Human Biology with a C- grade or better.</li>
<li>Psych 111-General Psychology with a C- grade or better.</li>
<li>Students must have a cumulative GPA of at least 2.5 in order to qualify for the Social Work program.</li>
</ol>Being a self declared Social Work major does not automaticaly admit you into the Social Work program.&nbsp; Ask your advisor about the application process.<br />
